Residents of Akure, the Ondo State capital on Wednesday stormed the streets to celebrate the declaration of Asiwaju Bola Tinubu as President-elect in last Saturday’s general election. Commercial motorcyclists, traders, taxi drivers and market women joined in the celebration. They stormed the secretariat of the APC where a cow was slaughtered as part of the celebration. One of the drivers, Mr Saliu Ojo, said he was optimistic that Nigerians would experience a new era of abundance and economic transformation. A community leader, High Chief Alaba Olaniyi Netufo, who is also an Executive Director at the Rural Electrification Agency, said the victory of the APC showed the people were happy with Governor Oluwarotimi Akeredolu. Read Also: My heart, door open to all – Tinubu Netufo who also congratulated Dr. Jimoh Ibrahim as Senator,-Elect for Ondo South Senatorial District said the victory was well deserved. He said the victory for All APC candidates at the polls was an indication that candidates of the party have the capacity to bring dividends of democracy to the people. State Chairman of the Ondo APC, Engr. Ade Adetimehin, said the party has proven that the state remained a progressive.